  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 615501dbe4f3fe94fbf4b564abb10237, type: 3}
  m_Name: ModConfig
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  id: MythicalPlates
  title: Mythical Plates
  author: thunder725
  description: "=-= This module pack is currently in Public Beta. It needs to be subscribed
    voluntarily to function. The up-to-date manuals are available in #mod-creation
    in the public KTANE Discord =-=\n\n\"The rightful bearer of a Plate draws from
    the Plate it holds.\"\n\nHarness the power of the Mythical Plates and defy the
    very fabric of reality!\n\n18 new challenges all centered around a mechanic of
    Void, combined with a cellular automaton, a tower defense game, a Rubik's Cube
    or a chain of plane flights.\n\nIf you feel adventurous, you can defy the Allmighty
    Sinnoh and solve 3 randomly-selected challenges in a row.\nOtherwise, they each
    are contained within their own individual Plate module.\n\nCreated by: thunder725\n\nIncludes
    the following 19 modules:\n- Allmighty Sinnoh\n- Blank Plate\n- Draco Plate\n-
    Dread Plate\n- Earth Plate\n- Fist Plate\n- Flame Plate\n- Icicle Plate\n- Insect
    Plate\n- Iron Plate\n- Meadow Plate\n- Mind Plate\n- Pixie Plate\n- Sky Plate\n-
    Splash Plate\n- Spooky Plate\n- Stone Plate\n- Toxic Plate\n- Zap Plate\n\nManuals
    can be found at https://ktane.timwi.de/\n\nIncludes Twitch Plays compatibility.\n\n=-=
    Version History =-=\n=-= 0.8\n- Open for Public Beta Testing\n\n=-= 0.8.1\n- Fixed
    Draco Plate and Blank Plate modules not having proper reset buttons.\n\n=-= 0.8.2\n-
    Pixie Plate: Fixed Ifle-Sym healing Demons when attacking them if its attack stat
    was negative.\n\n=-= 0.8.3\n- Pixie Plate: Void now affects player movement during
    the setup phase\n\n=-= 0.8.4\r\n- Allmighty Sinnoh: Fixed a bug where Step Two
    would not apply if only the Mark of Antimatter was affected.\r\n- Fist Plate:
    Made D5 and D7 unable to get Voided.\r\n- Blank Plate: Adjusted Path generation
    to be a shorter part of the module. Compressed Log for clearer explanations.\r\n-
    Sky Plate: Favorized path being affected by Voided Cities\r\nThanks Blan!\n\n=-=
    0.8.5\r\n- Sky Plate: Fixed several bugs in the puzzle generation, and rewrote
    Logging to be much clearer for players.\r\n- Iron Plate, Meadow Plate: Cleaned
    Logging by only including the final puzzle generation and not the aborted ones.\r\n-
    Dread Plate, Flame Plate, Splash Plate, Toxic Plate: Slightly tweaked logging\n\n=-=
    0.8.6\r\n- Allmighty Sinnoh: Made the Mark of Time wiggle more noticeable. Added
    TP command to get Mark of Time read if needed. Fixed TP command Plate sub-handler
    being treated as invalid by TP due to empty return.\r\n- Zap Plate: Fixed TP handler
    not working.\r\n- Dread Plate: Added \"press\" as a valid keyword for TP command
    submission.\n\n=-= 0.8.7\r\n- Zap Plate: Changed Table Looping behaviour to make
    the module slightly more interesting\r\n- Mind Plate: Made movement logging slightly
    more readable\r\n- Icicle Plate: Fixed incorrect logging of the last movement
    on a successful attempt"
  version: 0.8.7
  outputFolder: build
  debugBuild: 1
  previewImage: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 3435afec60dddb141ad5f45675da578c, type: 3}
